X_train_clf, X_test_clf, y_train_clf, y_test_clf = my_train_test_split(data,
                                                                       'Sold_in_30',

indices = np.random.permutation(len(X_test_reg) + len(X_train_reg))

X_clf, y_clf = pd.concat([X_test_clf, X_train_clf]).iloc[indices], pd.concat([y_test_clf, y_train_clf]).iloc[indices]

from pyearth import Earth
from sklearn.ensemble import AdaBoostRegressor
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

mars = Earth(max_degree=2, penalty=1.5)
mars = AdaBoostRegressor(base_estimator=mars, n_estimators=15, learning_rate=0.1, loss="exponential")

scores = cross_val_score(mars, X_reg, list(y_reg['Price']), scoring="neg_mean_squared_error", cv=5)
rmse_scores = np.sqrt(-scores)
np.mean(rmse_scores)
